Bare metal cloud is gaining significant traction in the global market due to its ability to provide dedicated and high-performance computing resources to organizations. The market is segmented based on components, organization size, verticals, and geography. By component, the market is classified into solutions and services. Solutions segment comprises networking, storage, and compute whereas service segment includes consulting, integration, and maintenance services. Organizational size segment includes small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) and large enterprises. In terms of verticals, the market caters to segments like banking, financial services, and insurance (BFSI), IT and ITES, government and public sector, retail and consumer goods, among others. Geographically, the market is analyzed across North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, South America, and the Middle East and Africa regions.

